.TH plfs_read 3 "${PACKAGE_STRING}" 
.SH NAME
plfs_read 
.SH SYNTAX
#include <plfs.h>
.PP
ssize_t plfs_read( Plfs_fd *, char *buf, size_t size, off_t offset );

.SH DESCRIPTION
Read up to 
.I size 
or EOF from file handle 
.I Plfs_fd 
into buffer. See 
.I read(2) 
for more information.  This call is thread-safe.

.SH INPUT PARAMETERS
.TP 1i
Plfs_fd
the file handle returned from plfs_open
.TP 1i
buf
Buffer to read into
.TP 1i
size
Size to read
.TP li
offset
Offset to start with

.SH RETURN VALUES
Most PLFS functions return 0 or -errno, except write and read
which return the number of bytes or -errno

